-symbol-is-not-%2Farticleshow%2F118151703.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Frow-over-kanye-wests-t-shirt-stop-calling-it-swastika-nazi-symbol-is-not-%2Famp_articleshow%2F118151703.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Frow-over-kanye-wests-t-shirt-stop-calling-it-swastika-nazi-symbol-is-not-%2Famp_articleshow%2F118151703.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Salman%20Rushdie%20describes%20attack%20that%20left%20him%20blinded%20in%20one%20eye%20as%20he%20testifies%20in%20court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739287620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-germany-frankfurt-salman-rushdie_6327931.jpg%3F20231020095321%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsalman-rushdie-trial-author-describes-moment-of-attack-as-he-gives-evidence-in-new-york-courtroom-13307273%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sir%20Salman%20Rushdie%20has%20described%20in%20court%20the%20moment%20he%20was%20attacked%20on%20stage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsalman-rushdie-trial-author-describes-moment-of-attack-as-he-gives-evidence-in-new-york-courtroom-13307273%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsalman-rushdie-trial-author-describes-moment-of-attack-as-he-gives-evidence-in-new-york-courtroom-13307273%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsalman-rushdie-trial-author-describes-moment-of-attack-as-he-gives-evidence-in-new-york-courtroom-13307273%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20Try%20To%20Build%20Mini%20Sun%20In%20France%2C%20With%20A%20Big%20India%20Link%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20will%20on%20Wednesday%20inspect%20the%20world's%20most%20advanced%20fusion%20energy%20nuclear%20reactor%20in%20Cadarache%20in%20southern%20France%2C%20where%20the%20world's%20best%20scientists%20have%20gathered%20to%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bminiature%20Sun%26quot%3B%20on%20Earth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20on%20a%20three-day%20visit%20to%20France%20from%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENamed%20the%20ITER%20(International%20Thermonuclear%20Experimental%20Reactor)%20or%20%26quot%3BThe%20Way%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20project%20seeks%20to%20provide%20the%20world%20an%20unlimited%20supply%20of%20clean%20energy%20and%20costs%20over%20Euro%2022%20billion.%20It%20is%20an%20unprecedented%20collaboration%20of%20seven%20nations%20-%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Japan%2C%20China%2C%20India%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20aim%20to%20create%20%26quot%3BAditya%20on%20Prithvi%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20has%20%26quot%3BMade%20In%20India%26quot%3B%20written%20all%20over%20it%2C%20and%20seeks%20to%20harness%20%26quot%3BMitra%20on%20Dharti%26quot%3B.%20By%20committing%20Rs%2017%2C500%20crores%20-%20about%2010%25%20of%20the%20cost%2C%20India%20will%20get%20100%25%20access%20to%20the%20technology.%20This%20is%20the%20most%20expensive%20mega-science%20effort%20India%20is%20participating%20in%20and%20globally%2C%20ITER%20is%20the%20most%20expensive%20science%20project%20to%20be%20undertaken%20in%20the%2021st%20century%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20also%20contributed%20the%20biggest%20component%20in%20the%20project%20-%20the%20world's%20largest%20refrigerator%20that%20houses%20this%20unique%20reactor%2C%20was%20made%20in%20Gujarat%20by%20Larsen%20%26amp%3B%20Toubro.%20It%20weighs%20over%203%2C800%20tonnes%20and%20is%20almost%20half%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Qutub%20Minar.%20The%20total%20weight%20of%20the%20ITER%20reactor%20will%20be%20about%2028%2C000%20tonnes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20India%20has%20also%20contributed%20%26quot%3Bin-kind%26quot%3B%20material%20manufactured%20by%20the%20Indian%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sun%20is%20a%20natural%20fusion%20energy%20cauldron%20and%20life%20on%20Earth%20would%20be%20impossible%20if%20solar%20energy%20came%20to%20a%20halt.%20There%20is%20a%20joke%20among%20scientists%20which%20says%20when%20will%20fusion%20energy%20be%20harnessed%2C%20and%20the%20timeline%20has%20always%20been%20after%20two%20decades%20since%20the%201980's.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20mega%20endeavour%20is%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20steps%20to%20harvest%20fusion%20energy%2C%20that%20is%2C%20generating%20energy%20by%20fusing%20atoms.%20Traditional%20atomic%20energy%20works%20by%20splitting%20atoms%20and%20it%20generates%20long%20lasting%20radioactive%20waste.%20But%20by%20fusing%20hydrogen%20and%20its%20sisters%2C%20the%20waste%20product%20is%20a%20benign%20Helium%20gas.%20The%20Sun%20generates%20its%20energy%20by%20fusing%20atoms%20and%20today%2C%20when%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20bearing%20upon%20us%2C%20the%20search%20for%20a%20clean%2C%20carbon-free%20source%20of%20energy%20has%20become%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%20But%20creating%20the%20Sun%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20a%20massive%20reactor%20is%20being%20made%20at%20Cadarache%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20is%20taking%20care%20of%2045%25%20of%20the%20construction%20cost%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20member%20nations%20are%20sharing%209.1%25%20of%20the%20cost%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20over%20a%20million%20different%20parts%20which%20will%20be%20sourced%20from%20over%2045%20countries%20and%20it%20is%20now%20estimated%20that%20by%202035%2C%20the%20ITER%20machine%20will%20be%20ready%20for%20its%20first%20full%20experimental%20run.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20concern%20with%20India's%20involvement%20in%20ITER%20-%20the%20dismal%20allocation%20of%20human%20resources%20by%20India%20at%20the%20site.%20As%20per%20an%20agreement%2C%20each%20participating%20country%20can%20provide%20up%20to%2010%25%20of%20the%20staff.%20Thus%2C%20India%20can%20send%20about%20100%20of%20its%20engineers%20and%20scientists%20to%20work%20as%20staff%20at%20ITER.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecords%20showed%20that%20only%2025%20to%2030%20Indians%20are%20currently%20working%20at%20the%20site.%20To%20have%20a%20full%20staff%20strength%20is%20important%20so%20that%20young%20Indian%20engineers%20can%20learn%20the%20complexities%20of%20this%20million%20piece%20jigsaw%20puzzle%20that%20is%20being%20put%20together.%20While%20India%20will%20no%20doubt%20have%20full%20access%20to%20drawings%20and%20blueprints%2C%20Indians%20who%20have%20worked%20on%20the%20site%20say%20the%20best%20learning%20comes%20by%20dirtying%20one's%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20not%20meeting%20the%20staff%20strength%2C%20India%20has%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20countries%20like%20China%20to%20have%20excess%20staffing.%20There%20are%20several%20reasons%20behind%20the%20understaffing%2C%20most%20of%20them%20related%20to%20myopic%20policies%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Training%20(DOPT).%20There%20is%20a%20general%20circular%20that%20states%20that%20government%20staff%20cannot%20be%20posted%20overseas%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20and%20for%20experts%20from%20autonomous%20institutes%2C%20for%20terms%20not%20exceeding%20five%20years.%20For%20a%20project%20that%20has%20a%20gestation%20of%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20such%20short%20tenures%20are%20counter-productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20bureaucracy%20needs%20to%20make%20an%20exception%20and%20the%20one-size-fits-all-regulation%20needs%20to%20go%20if%20India%20really%20wants%20to%20learn%20the%20art%20and%20science%20of%20making%20the%20ITER%20machine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739287140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2F20ccuhtg_iter_625x300_11_February_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%